5|$|During January 19–21 the <b>Soviet</b> <b>forces</b> {{eliminated}} the encircled German forces {{and tried to}} expand their offensive southward towards Siniavino. However, the 18th Army significantly reinforced its positions there with the SS Police, 21st Infantry, and soon after the 11th Infantry and 28th Mountain Divisions. The <b>Soviet</b> <b>forces</b> captured Workers Settlement No. 6 but were unable to advance any further.|$|E
5|$|During the Battle of Sevastopol, the Stukas {{repeatedly}} {{bombed the}} trapped <b>Soviet</b> <b>forces.</b> Some Ju 87 pilots flew up to 300 sorties against the Soviet defenders. Luftflotte 4's StG 77 flew 7,708 combat sorties dropping 3,537 tonnes of bombs on the city. Their efforts help secure the capitulation of <b>Soviet</b> <b>forces</b> on 4 July.|$|E
